Police fired teargas to disperse protesters on Moi Avenue, Nairobi on Monday.The group, working under the slogan #TakeBackKenya, had gathered near Tom Mboya statue. Three people were arrested in the protest meant to denounce corruption in the country.Read: Bribery, nepotism, tenders lead in county corruption The resilient protesters rushed to Jeevanjee Gardens where it was reported they planned another march through the city.The group are up in arms against what they termed 'daily plundering of public funds by government officials' through corruption.Read: Uhuru, Ruto's office perceived to be most corrupt - InfotrackAlso read: 'Cry baby' Uhuru faces KOT wrath after corruption frustrationThe protest's organisers said they had notified police of the march through a letter on December 6.